HEADWORD: Anallantoidea
<hw>An`al*lan*toid"e*a</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>'an</grk> priv. + E. <ets>allantoidea</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>The division of Vertebrata in which no allantois
is developed. It includes amphibians, fishes, and lower forms.</def>⟦br⟧
